      "schema:name": "Food Standards Agency Phytoplankton monitoring",
      "schema:url": "https://www.food.gov.uk/business-guidance/biotoxin-and-phytoplankton-monitoring",
      "schema:description": "In accordance with EU and Retained EU legislation, competent authorities shall periodically monitor classified production and relaying areas in order to check for the presence of toxin-producing plankton in production and relaying waters and marine biotoxins in live bivalve molluscs. Water samples are collected from sampling locations within classified production and relaying areas and analysed for various species of phytoplankton including:\r\n• Alexandrium\r\n• Dinophysis\r\n• Pseudo-nitzschia\r\nPeriodic monitoring for phytoplankton provides an early warning of toxic events and also helps to inform the competent authority’s or local authorities additional monitoring activities.",
